在2015年飛到[[穀神星|穀神星]]的[[曙光號|曙光號]]在這顆矮行星的表面發現了幾個明亮的特徵（也稱為[[光斑|光斑]]）。 

最亮的群集稱為"亮點 5"，位於{{convert|80|km|mi|adj=on|sp=us}}的[[歐卡托撞擊坑|歐卡托撞擊坑]]<ref name="USGS-20150713-pdf">{{cite web |author=Staff |title=USGS: Ceres nomenclature |url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/images/ceres.pdf |date=13 July 2015 |work=[[USGS|USGS]] |format=[[PDF|PDF]] |accessdate=16 July 2015 |archive-date=2015-11-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151115202652/http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/images/ceres.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="USGS-20150706">{{cite web |author=Staff |title=Planetary Names: Crater, craters: Occator on Ceres |url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/15341 |date=6 July 2015 |work=[[USGS|USGS]] |accessdate=16 July 2015 |archive-date=2015-09-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150905103216/http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/15341 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。群集最大和最亮的元件位於火山口的中心，較暗的斑點靠近坑的東部邊緣。當早期，''曙光號''在軌道的階段時，這些高反照率的斑點被推測是某種[[釋氣|釋氣]]<ref name=Lakdawalla20150319>{{Cite web |url=http://www.planetary.org/blogs/emily-lakdawalla/2015/03191629-lpsc-2015-dawn-at-ceres.html |title=LPSC 2015: First results from Dawn at Ceres: provisional place names and possible plumes |accessdate=2015-10-16 |archive-date=2016-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160506035930/http://www.planetary.org/blogs/emily-lakdawalla/2015/03191629-lpsc-2015-dawn-at-ceres.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，NASA在稍後推斷這些明亮的區域是返回的高反射性物質，並且建議可能是冰和鹽類<ref name='not ice'>{{cite news |last=Feltman |first=Rachel |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/news/speaking-of-science/wp/2015/07/10/the-weird-white-spots-on-ceres-might-not-be-ice-after-all/ |title=The weird white spots on Ceres might not be ice after all |work=The Washington Pot |date=July 10, 2015 |accessdate=2015-07-24 |archive-date=2015-07-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150723092049/http://www.washingtonpost.com/news/speaking-of-science/wp/2015/07/10/the-weird-white-spots-on-ceres-might-not-be-ice-after-all/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。這些明亮的特徵[[反照率|反照率]]大約為40%，比穀神星表面的平均亮了4倍<ref name=siliconvalleyastrolecture>{{cite speech
 |title=Now Appearing At a Dwarf Planet Near You: NASA's Dawn Mission to the Asteroid Belt
 |first=Marc
