}} </ref>。

== 亮點 5 ==
{{further|歐卡托撞擊坑}}
最亮的群集（"亮點 5"），位於直徑{{convert|80|km|mi|adj=on|sp=us}}的[[歐卡托撞擊坑|歐卡托]]坑<ref name="USGS-20150713-pdf"/><ref name="USGS-20150706"/>，它的座標位置是緯度19.86° N；經度238.85 E<ref name="USGS-20150713-pdf" /><ref name="USGS-20150706" />。

[[斯威本科技大學|斯威本大學]]的阿倫·杜菲（Alan Duffy）建議是"隕石撞擊或搖撼覆蓋的材料，使底下的冰或鹽水被加熱，因此鹽水形成間歇噴泉。現在，水分逃逸進入太空，只有鹽份留了下來<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://cosmosmagazine.com/space/what-ceres-are-those-bright-spots |title=A. Duffy – Cosmos – What on Ceres are those bright spots? |accessdate=2015-10-16 |archive-date=2015-10-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151015222156/https://cosmosmagazine.com/space/what-ceres-are-those-bright-spots |dead-url=no }}</ref>"。一層薄霧大約填滿了歐卡托撞擊坑的一半，但是沒有擴展至它的邊緣<ref name=presentation>Chris Russel at {{cite web |url=http://nesf2015.arc.nasa.gov/agenda |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2015-07-25 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150724072209/http://nesf2015.arc.nasa.gov/agenda |archivedate=2015-07-24 }}</ref>，定期出現環繞著亮點 5，最著名的亮點；這更加證實了是某種[[釋氣|釋氣]]或出現火山活動的想法<ref>{{cite news |last=Rivkin |first=Andrew |url=http://www.planetary.org/blogs/guest-blogs/2015/0721-dawn-at-ceres-a-haze-in-occator-rivkin.html |title=Dawn at Ceres: A haze in Occator crater? |work=The Planetary Society |date=21 July 2015 |accessdate=2015-07-24 |archive-date=2016-05-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160514052923/http://www.planetary.org/blogs/guest-blogs/2015/0721-dawn-at-ceres-a-haze-in-occator-rivkin.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.planetary.org/blogs/guest-blogs/2015/0721-dawn-at-ceres-a-haze-in-occator-rivkin.html |title=Dawn at Ceres: A haze in Occator crater? Posted by Andrew Rivkin |accessdate=2015-10-16 |archive-date=2016-05-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160514052923/http://www.planetary.org/blogs/guest-blogs/2015/0721-dawn-at-ceres-a-haze-in-occator-rivkin.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

''曙光號''的影像導致媒體，包括天文雜誌<ref name="S&T-3 March 2015">{{cite web |last=Beatty |first=Kelly |title=Bright Spots on Ceres Intrigue Scientists |url=http://www.skyandtelescope.com/astronomy-news/bright-spots-on-ceres-03032015/ |date=3 March 2015 |work=[[Sky_&_Telescope|Sky & Telescope]] |accessdate=2 June 2015 |archive-date=2015-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924102542/http://www.skyandtelescope.com/astronomy-news/bright-spots-on-ceres-03032015/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>和科學雜誌<ref name="SA-20150318">{{cite web |last=Witze |first=Alexandra |title=Bright Spots on Ceres Could Be Active Ice |url=http://www.scientificamerican.com/article/bright-spots-on-ceres-could-be-active-ice1/ |date=18 March 2015 |work=[[Scientific_American|Scientific American]] |accessdate=2 June 2015 |archive-date=2015-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924141640/http://www.scientificamerican.com/article/bright-spots-on-ceres-could-be-active-ice1/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>的廣泛報導，包括這些亮點新的來源<ref name="BBC-20150302">{{cite news |last=Amos |first=Jonathan |title=Bright spotlight on Dawn mission to Ceres |url=http://www.bbc.com/news/science-environment-31702639 |date=2 March 2015 |work=[[BBC_News|BBC News]] |accessdate=2 June 2015 |archive-date=2015-10-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016215123/http://www.bbc.com/news/science-environment-31702639 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，。NASA在5月份進行非正式的民意調查，提供這些斑點性質的一些想法<ref name="NASA-201505-poll">{{cite web |author=Staff |title=What's the spot on World Ceres? |url=http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/dawn/world_ceres |date=25 May 2015 |work=[[NASA|NASA]] |accessdate=25 May 2015 |archive-date=2015-10-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151015104349/http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/dawn/world_ceres/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>：冰、火山、間歇泉、鹽類礦床、岩石或其它<ref name="SP-20150522">{{cite web |last=Cofield |first=Calla |title=What Are Those Bright Spots on Ceres? Go Vote! |url=http://www.space.com/29469-ceres-bright-spots-nasa-vote.html |date=22 May 2015 |work=[[Space.com|Space.com]] |accessdate=25 May 2015 |archive-date=2015-09-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150929223918/http://www.space.com/29469-ceres-bright-spots-nasa-vote.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

小行星專家，A. Rivkin，在''[[天空與望遠鏡雜誌|天空與望遠鏡雜誌]]''的一篇文章中指出，在低角度可以看見陰霾在火山口中，而不是在外面，可以推測這可能是由冰昇華的蒸汽，或許可以和亮點聯結在一起<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.skyandtelescope.com/astronomy-news/ceres-bright-spots-and-more-072920155/ |title=Sky and Telescope magazine - Dawn Sees Ceres Bright Spots and More By Emily Poore  July 30, 2015 |accessdate=2015-10-16 |archive-date=2015-10-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001110709/http://www.skyandtelescope.com/astronomy-news/ceres-bright-spots-and-more-072920155/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2015年9月對反照率的研究表明斑點可能是鹽而不是冰，這意味著在某種程度上，穀神星的內部會像表面提供新鮮的鹽<ref>[http://gizmodo.com/ceres-mysterious-bright-spots-arent-made-of-ice-after-a-1734112941 Ceres' Mysterious Bright Spots Aren't Made of Ice After All] {{Wayback|url=http://gizmodo.com/ceres-mysterious-bright-spots-arent-made-of-ice-after-a-1734112941 |date=20151017033730 }}. ''Gizmodo'', 1 October 2015</ref>。

